Use samplingMethod/GeologicSamplingProcess to indicate the process used to obtain or create the GeologicSpecimen. eg: diamond drilling percussion drilling piston core drilling vibro core drilling channel sampling sea floor dredging crushing thin section mineral separation melting geological hammer, etc
IsotopicEventType vocabulary would include terms like: closure isotopic mixing Pb loss etc

For geological specimens, processingDetails should reflect what was done to a specimen to derive other (child) specimens. eg; crushing, splitting, thin section, mineral separation, electron beam zapping. Or could xlink:href to a source (eg, a url) documenting a standard operating procedure.
NOTE: ISO xml schema for valueUnit imports 19136 GML units:UnitDefinition, not 19103 UnitsOfMeasure:UnitOfMeasure

propertyType must be an attribute of the feature of interest eg: Earth material for lithological description of rock specimen eg: Chemical composition for geochemical or geochronological analysis of a specimen. Need to create a suitable property type.

Use GeoSciML to describe event age, process and environment. e.g, Event age = 350 Ma +/- 3 Ma. Event process = intrusion, extrusion, granulite metamorphism. Event environment = plutonic, marine.
